This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new framework for object detection that combines region-based and region-free methodologies, which involves designing a new architecture and optimizing a multi-task loss function. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the network for speed, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
